name: Lincoln for Obama  44" x 62.875"
description:
Political Art - Lincoln took the first step, making it possible for Barack Obama to be voted as the next President of the United States.  In his famous Gettysburg address he redefined the Civil War as a struggle not merely for the Union, but as "a new birth of freedom" that would bring true equality to all of its citizens. The seed was planted many years ago.  This is Lincoln's new victory portrait for 2008.

Printed on heavy 100% cotton fiber archival grade paper, neutral pH, the print is acid-free and chlorine-free as is essential with fine art prints.

"wallnut.bigcartel.com" does not appear on the printed artwork
